## 11. Breakpoint Changes

PatternFly 6 uses **rem units** for breakpoints instead of pixels.

| Breakpoint | PF6 Token | Old (px) | New (rem) |
|---|---|---|---|
| xs | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--xs` | 0px | 0rem |
| sm | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--sm` | 576px | 36rem |
| md | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--md` | 768px | 48rem |
| lg | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--lg` | 992px | 62rem |
| xl | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--xl` | 1200px | 75rem |
| 2xl | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--2xl` | 1450px | 90.625rem |

### Action Items:
- [ ] Search for pixel-based breakpoint logic in JavaScript/TypeScript
- [ ] Convert pixel breakpoint comparisons to rem (divide by 16)
- [ ] Update any `matchMedia` or `resize` listeners that use pixel breakpoints

