## 1. Prerequisites

### React Version Requirements
- **React**: `^17 || ^18 || ^19` (all three major versions supported)
- **React DOM**: `^17 || ^18 || ^19`
- **Node.js**: >= 10 (for running codemods)

### Before Starting
- [ ] **Complete PF4→PF5 migration first** if not already done (see [v5-archive.patternfly.org](https://v5-archive.patternfly.org/get-started/upgrade))
- [ ] Commit all current work — migration will touch many files
- [ ] Ensure your test suite passes on PF5 before starting

---

## 2. Package Upgrades

Update all `@patternfly/*` packages to their v6 equivalents:

| Package | PF5 Major Version | PF6 Target Version |
|---------|-------------------|---------------------|
| `@patternfly/react-core` | 5.x.x | **6.x.x** (latest: 6.5.1) |
| `@patternfly/react-table` | 5.x.x | **6.x.x** (latest: 6.5.1) |
| `@patternfly/react-icons` | 5.x.x | **6.x.x** (latest: 6.5.1) |
| `@patternfly/react-tokens` | 5.x.x | **6.x.x** (latest: 6.5.1) |
| `@patternfly/react-styles` | 5.x.x | **6.x.x** (latest: 6.5.1) |
| `@patternfly/react-charts` | 7.x.x | **8.x.x** (latest: 8.5.1) |
| `@patternfly/patternfly` (CSS) | 5.x.x | **6.x.x** (latest: 6.5.2) |
| `@patternfly/react-component-groups` | 5.x.x | **6.x.x** (latest: 6.5.0) |

### Codemod Tool
| Package | Version |
|---------|---------|
| `@patternfly/pf-codemods` | latest (2.6.3) — run via `npx`, not installed |

### Victory Charts (Optional Peer Dependency)
If using charts, install Victory packages separately:
- Option A: `npm install victory` (all features)
- Option B: Install specific packages: `victory-core`, `victory-tooltip`, etc.

---

## 3. Migration Steps Overview

Execute in this **exact order**:

1. **Update dependencies** in `package.json` to PF6 versions
2. **Run codemods** (before any manual changes!)
3. **Remove/update CSS overrides** (old `pf-v5` variables won't work)
4. **Review and update variable/class names** (tokens codemod + manual)
5. **Update pixel-based breakpoint logic** (PF6 uses rem units)
6. **Fix remaining build errors manually**
7. **Update tests**

---

## 4. Codemods — What They Fix vs Manual Work

### Running Codemods

```bash
# Step 1: Preview issues (no changes made)
npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest <path-to-src> --v6

# Step 2: Auto-fix what can be fixed
npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest <path-to-src> --v6 --fix

# Step 3: Run class-name-updater for CSS class renames (pf-v5 → pf-v6)
npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest <path-to-src> --v6 --fix  # class-name-updater

# Step 4: Run tokens-update for React token / CSS variable renames
# (updates global CSS vars in .js/.tsx files)

# Step 5: Run css-vars-updater for non-React files (.css, .scss, .md)
# See: github.com/patternfly/pf-codemods/tree/main/packages/css-vars-updater

# Step 6: Clean up data-codemods markers
npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest <path-to-src> --v6 --fix --only data-codemods-cleanup

# For large codebases:
NODE_OPTIONS=--max-old-space-size=4096 npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest <path-to-src> --v6 --fix
```

### ✅ What Codemods Handle Automatically

| Change | Auto-Fixed? | Notes |
|--------|:-----------:|-------|
| Prop renames (e.g., `isActive` → `isClicked` on Button) | ✅ | |
| Prop removals (e.g., `isFlat`, `isRounded` from Card) | ✅ | Removes the prop |
| Import path updates (deprecated → `/deprecated`) | ✅ | |
| `EmptyStateHeader` → props on `EmptyState` | ✅ Partial | Complex cases need manual review |
| Old Modal → `/deprecated` import | ✅ | |
| Next Modal → main import | ✅ | |
| Charts import path (`@patternfly/react-charts` → `/victory`) | ✅ | |
| `pf-v5` class prefix → `pf-v6` | ✅ | Simple find/replace; verify results |
| Nav `variant="tertiary"` → `variant="horizontal-subnav"` | ✅ | |
| Page `header` prop → `masthead` | ✅ | |
| PageSection `variant` values (dark, etc.) | ✅ | Removes unsupported values |
| PageSection `type="nav"` removal | ✅ | |
| PageSidebar `theme` prop removal | ✅ | |
| Banner `variant` → `color` | ✅ | May need manual review |
| Label color renames (`cyan`→`teal`, `gold`→`yellow`) | ✅ | |
| Chip → Label replacement | ✅ | |
| KebabToggle → MenuToggle replacement | ✅ | |
| `isLabelBeforeButton` → `labelPosition="start"` | ✅ | |
| Switch `labelOff` prop removal | ✅ | |
| CSS variable renames (global vars like spacers, font-size) | ✅ | Closest match |
| React token renames (`global_FontSize_lg` → `t_global_font_size_lg`) | ✅ | |

### ⚠️ What Requires Manual Work

| Change | Why Manual? |
|--------|------------|
| **EmptyState complex refactoring** | Codemods handle basic cases, but custom layouts/icons may need manual adjustment |
| **Modal migration to new API** | Codemods move old Modal to `/deprecated`; adopting new Modal API is manual |
| **CSS color variable replacements** | Color tokens updated to hot pink placeholder (`--pf-t--temp--dev--tbd`) — you must manually pick correct token |
| **React tokens with no 1:1 match** | e.g., `global_link_Color_hover` has no direct PF6 equivalent |
| **Custom CSS overrides** | All `pf-v5` overrides must be reviewed; many have no PF6 equivalent |
| **Removed deprecated components** | Application Launcher, Context Selector, old Dropdown, Options Menu, Page Header, old Select — must rewrite |
| **Tile → Card migration** | No auto-fixer; manual rewrite needed |
| **Button icon children → `icon` prop** | Partial fix for `variant="plain"` only |
| **Test updates** | Snapshot tests, DOM queries, aria-attribute checks |

---

## 5. Key Component API Changes

### EmptyState (Major Refactoring)
```jsx
// ❌ PF5 — EmptyStateHeader & EmptyStateIcon are separate components
<EmptyState>
  <EmptyStateHeader
    titleText="Empty state"
    headingLevel="h4"
    icon={<EmptyStateIcon icon={CubesIcon} />}
  />
  <EmptyStateBody>Body text</EmptyStateBody>
</EmptyState>

// ✅ PF6 — Header/Icon props moved INTO EmptyState
<EmptyState titleText="Empty state" headingLevel="h4" icon={CubesIcon}>
  <EmptyStateBody>Body text</EmptyStateBody>
</EmptyState>
```
- `EmptyStateHeader` and `EmptyStateIcon` **no longer exported**
- `titleText`, `headingLevel`, `icon` are now props on `<EmptyState>`
- Icon is passed as the component reference (not wrapped in `<EmptyStateIcon>`)
- ⚠️ Codemods handle basic cases but **complex layouts need manual review**

### Modal (Deprecated + New Implementation)
```jsx
// ❌ PF5 — Old Modal (now at /deprecated)
import { Modal } from "@patternfly/react-core";
// Codemod moves to:
import { Modal } from "@patternfly/react-core/deprecated";

// ✅ PF6 — New Modal (was previously at /next)
import { Modal } from "@patternfly/react-core"; // promoted from /next
```
- Old Modal API moved to `@patternfly/react-core/deprecated`
- The `/next` Modal implementation is now the primary/promoted one
- **Recommendation**: Migrate to the new Modal API (composable pattern)
- The new Modal uses a different composition pattern — **manual migration required**

### PageSection
```jsx
// ❌ PF5
<PageSection variant="dark" />
<PageSection variant={PageSectionVariants.dark} />
<PageSection type="nav" />

// ✅ PF6
<PageSection />  // variant only accepts "default" or "secondary"
<PageSection />  // type="nav" removed
```
- `variant` prop now only accepts `"default"` or `"secondary"`
- Old values (`dark`, `light`, etc.) removed — codemods remove the prop
- `type="nav"` removed
- Variant classes only applied when `type="default"`

### Page
```jsx
// ❌ PF5
<Page header={<Masthead />} tertiaryNav={nav} isTertiaryNavGrouped isTertiaryNavWidthLimited />

// ✅ PF6
<Page masthead={<Masthead />} horizontalSubnav={nav} isHorizontalSubnavGrouped isHorizontalSubnavWidthLimited />
```
- `header` → `masthead`
- `tertiaryNav` → `horizontalSubnav`
- `isTertiaryNavGrouped` → `isHorizontalSubnavGrouped`
- `isTertiaryNavWidthLimited` → `isHorizontalSubnavWidthLimited`
- Markup changes when `horizontalSubnav` or `breadcrumb` props are passed (PageBody wrapper added)

### Button
```jsx
// ❌ PF5
<Button isActive>Click</Button>
<Button variant="plain"><SomeIcon /></Button>

// ✅ PF6
<Button isClicked>Click</Button>
<Button variant="plain" icon={<SomeIcon />} />
```
- `isActive` → `isClicked`
- Icons must use the `icon` prop instead of being children
- `isDisabled` now sets `disabled` attr (not `aria-disabled`) for native buttons
- `aria-disabled` only renders when `true` (not when `false`)
- Button text wrapped in a `<span>` — affects `byText` queries

### Card
```jsx
// ❌ PF5 — These props removed:
<Card isSelectableRaised isDisabledRaised hasSelectableInput isFlat isRounded
      selectableInputAriaLabel="label" onSelectableInputChange={fn} />

// ✅ PF6 — Use built-in styling
<Card />
```
- Removed: `isSelectableRaised`, `isDisabledRaised`, `hasSelectableInput`, `selectableInputAriaLabel`, `onSelectableInputChange`, `isFlat`, `isRounded`
- Clickable card markup updated; `selectableActions.name` and `selectableActions.selectableActionId` no longer needed for clickable-only cards

### Nav
```jsx
// ❌ PF5
<Nav variant="tertiary" theme="dark" />

// ✅ PF6
<Nav variant="horizontal-subnav" />  // theme prop removed
```

### Banner
```jsx
// ❌ PF5
<Banner variant="red" />

// ✅ PF6
<Banner color="red" />  // or use status prop
```
- `variant` replaced with `color` or `status` props
- Colors renamed: `cyan` → `teal`, `gold` → `yellow`

### Label
- `isOverflowLabel` → `variant="overflow"`
- Colors renamed: `cyan` → `teal`, `gold` → `yellow`

### Accordion
- `AccordionContent` `isHidden` prop removed (auto-managed by `isExpanded`)
- `AccordionToggle` `isExpanded` prop moved to `AccordionItem`
- New `div` wrapper element in AccordionItem

### Checkbox / Radio
- `isLabelBeforeButton` → `labelPosition="start"`

### Switch
- `labelOff` prop removed (label should not change based on state)

### ExpandableSection
- `isActive` prop removed

### Avatar
- `border` prop removed → use `isBordered` instead

### DrawerContent
- `colorVariant="no-background"` removed; `"primary"` value added
- Use `DrawerContentColorVariant` enum (not `DrawerColorVariant`)

### Text → Content
- `Text` component renamed to `Content`
- `TextContent`, `TextList`, `TextListItem` → use `Content` equivalents

### Dropdown (Legacy)
- Old `Dropdown` from `@patternfly/react-core/deprecated` is **fully removed**
- Must migrate to composable Dropdown or Dropdown template

### Popper-based Components (Dropdown, Select, Popper)
- Default `appendTo` changed to `document.body`

---

## 6. CSS Variable / Token Changes

### Naming Convention Change
```
PF5: --pf-v5-global--FontSize--lg          →  PF6: --pf-t--global--font--size--lg
PF5: --pf-v5-c-button--...                 →  PF6: --pf-v6-c-button--...
PF5: global_FontSize_lg (React token)      →  PF6: t_global_font_size_lg
PF5: pf-v5-c-button (CSS class)            →  PF6: pf-v6-c-button
```

### Key Changes
- **Class prefix**: `pf-v5-` → `pf-v6-` (all CSS classes)
- **Global variables**: Complete restructure from `--pf-v5-global--*` to design token system `--pf-t--global--*`
- **Component variables**: `--pf-v5-c-*` → `--pf-v6-c-*`
- **React tokens**: Import from `@patternfly/react-tokens` — naming changed significantly

### Token Migration Tools

| Tool | Handles | File Types |
|------|---------|------------|
| **Main codemods** (`pf-codemods --v6`) | React component prop changes | `.js`, `.jsx`, `.ts`, `.tsx` |
| **class-name-updater** | `pf-v5-` → `pf-v6-` class prefixes | All file types |
| **tokens-update** | Global CSS vars & React tokens in code | `.js`, `.tsx` |
| **css-vars-updater** | CSS variables in stylesheets | `.css`, `.scss`, `.md`, custom |

### Color Tokens — Manual Work Required
- The tokens-update codemod replaces color variables with a **hot pink placeholder**: `--pf-t--temp--dev--tbd` (or `t_temp_dev_tbd` for React tokens)
- You must **manually** replace these with the correct PF6 design token
- Non-color globals (spacers, font sizes, box shadows) get auto-matched to closest value

### Reference Spreadsheets
- [Removed variables](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/e/2PACX-1vQqeH7ThYi0jkhYEB8B2SXa7x8AaY5T9ajG6o-Ogz3p7YVp0OuTulb_L3DYLDrHlY4zUE3IBiup6tkN/pubhtml?gid=1160160856&single=true)
- [Added variables](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/e/2PACX-1vQqeH7ThYi0jkhYEB8B2SXa7x8AaY5T9ajG6o-Ogz3p7YVp0OuTulb_L3DYLDrHlY4zUE3IBiup6tkN/pubhtml?gid=268831450&single=true)
- [All PF6 design tokens](https://www.patternfly.org/tokens/all-patternfly-tokens)

---

## 7. Breakpoint Changes

PF6 uses **rem units** instead of pixels for breakpoints:

| Breakpoint | Design Token | PF5 (px) | PF6 (rem) |
|------------|-------------|----------|-----------|
| xs | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--xs` | 0px | 0rem |
| sm | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--sm` | 576px | 36rem |
| md | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--md` | 768px | 48rem |
| lg | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--lg` | 992px | 62rem |
| xl | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--xl` | 1200px | 75rem |
| 2xl | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--2xl` | 1450px | 90.625rem |

**Action**: If you have pixel-based breakpoint logic in JavaScript, divide by 16 to get rem equivalent.

---

## 8. Deprecated & Removed Components

### Deprecated (moved to `/deprecated` import path)
- [ ] `Chip` → use `Label` instead
- [ ] `Tile` → use `Card` instead
- [ ] Old `Modal` → use new Modal (promoted from `/next`)
- [ ] `DragDrop`, `Droppable`, `Draggable` → use `DragDropSort` from `@patternfly/react-drag-drop`

### Fully Removed (no auto-fixer — must rewrite)
- [ ] `Application Launcher` → use custom menu pattern
- [ ] `Context Selector` → use custom menu pattern
- [ ] Old `Dropdown` (from deprecated) → use composable Dropdown
- [ ] `Options Menu` → use composable Select
- [ ] `Page Header` → use Masthead + Toolbar
- [ ] Old `Select` (from deprecated) → use composable Select
- [ ] `KebabToggle` → use `MenuToggle` with `variant="plain"` and `EllipsisVIcon`

### Renamed Components
- [ ] `Text` / `TextContent` / `TextList` / `TextListItem` → `Content`
- [ ] `ContentHeader` (component-groups) → `PageHeader`
- [ ] `InvalidObject` (component-groups) → `MissingPage`
- [ ] `NotAuthorized` (component-groups) → `UnauthorizedAccess`

---

## 9. Charts Migration

### Import Path Change
```jsx
// ❌ PF5
import { Chart } from '@patternfly/react-charts';

// ✅ PF6
import { Chart } from '@patternfly/react-charts/victory';
```

### Victory as Optional Peer Dependency
Victory is no longer bundled — install separately:
```bash
# All features:
npm install victory

# Or specific packages:
npm install victory-core victory-tooltip
```

---

## 10. Test Failures to Expect

### Button
- **`aria-disabled` not found**: PF6 uses `disabled` attribute instead of `aria-disabled` for native buttons. `aria-disabled` only renders when `true`.
- **`byText` queries fail**: Button text now wrapped in `<span>`. Use `byRole('button', { name: 'text' })` instead.

### Select
- **`byRole` queries fail**: Popper menu may be `aria-disabled` after selection in tests. Pass `{ hidden: true }` option or use `appendTo="inline"`.

### General
- **Snapshot tests**: Will break due to class name changes (`pf-v5` → `pf-v6`) and markup changes
- **CSS class selectors in tests**: Must update `pf-v5-*` → `pf-v6-*`
- **OUIA component types**: Updated from `PF5/` to `PF6/` prefix

---

## 11. Post-Migration Cleanup

- [ ] Run `--only data-codemods-cleanup` to remove `data-codemods` attributes/comments added by codemods
- [ ] Search for `--pf-t--temp--dev--tbd` (hot pink placeholders) and replace with correct design tokens
- [ ] Search for `t_temp_dev_tbd` in React code and replace with correct tokens
- [ ] Remove any remaining `pf-v5` references in CSS/SCSS files
- [ ] Verify all CSS overrides work with new token system
- [ ] Update snapshot tests
- [ ] Visual regression testing (PF6 includes significant visual/theme changes)
- [ ] Remove unused imports (especially `EmptyStateHeader`, `EmptyStateIcon`)

---

## Quick Reference: Codemod Commands

```bash
# 1. Preview all issues
npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest ./src --v6

# 2. Auto-fix issues
npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest ./src --v6 --fix

# 3. Run specific rule only
npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest ./src --v6 --fix --only <rule-name>

# 4. Exclude specific rules
npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest ./src --v6 --fix --exclude <rule-name>

# 5. Cleanup data-codemods markers (run LAST)
npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest ./src --v6 --fix --only data-codemods-cleanup

# 6. Large codebase
NODE_OPTIONS=--max-old-space-size=4096 npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest ./src --v6 --fix
```

