<!-- 6. DETAILED ANALYSIS -->
<!-- ============================================================ -->
<div id="detailed" class="section-anchor"></div>
<h2>🔍 Detailed Analysis</h2>

<!-- Package Upgrades -->
<details>
  <summary>📦 Package Upgrades <span class="badge badge-green">Winner: semver/goose</span></summary>
  <div class="details-body">
    <h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>PatternFly 6 requires updating all <code>@patternfly/*</code> packages to v6.x. The base <code>main</code> branch already has PF6 packages (<code>@patternfly/react-core: ^6.4.0</code>) but still runs React 17.0.2 in production dependencies. PF6 supports React 17, 18, and 19, but React 18 is recommended for full compatibility and future-proofing. Victory chart packages are now optional peer dependencies.</p>

    <table>
      <tr><th>Change</th><th><code>pf-codemods</code></th><th><code>semver/goose</code></th></tr>
      <tr class="comparison-row">
        <td>React version upgrade</td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-red">Not done</span><br>React stays at 17.0.2</td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-green">Done</span><br><code>react: ^18.3.1</code>, <code>@types/react: ^18.3.0</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr class="comparison-row">
        <td>Victory peer dependencies</td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-red">Not done</span></td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-green">Done</span><br>18 Victory packages added as devDependencies</td>
      </tr>
      <tr class="comparison-row">
        <td>Type patch script</td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-muted">N/A</span></td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-green">Added</span><br><code>patches/apply-type-patches.sh</code> — fixes SDK type incompatibilities for React 18</td>
      </tr>
      <tr class="comparison-row">
        <td>yarn.lock updated</td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-red">No</span></td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-green">Yes</span></td>
      </tr>
    </table>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- PageSection Changes -->
<details>
  <summary>📄 PageSection Migration <span class="badge badge-orange">Mixed — different strategies</span></summary>
  <div class="details-body">
    <h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>In PF6, <code>PageSection</code> variant only accepts <code>"default"</code> or <code>"secondary"</code>. The <code>PageSectionVariants</code> enum is still exported but only with these two values. The <code>hasBodyWrapper</code> prop (beta) controls whether children are wrapped in a <code>PageBody</code>. The <code>type="nav"</code> prop was removed.</p>

    <h4>pf-codemods approach</h4>
    <pre><code>// Added hasBodyWrapper={false} to 22 PageSection instances
&lt;PageSection hasBodyWrapper={false}
  variant={PageSectionVariants.default}&gt;
  ...
&lt;/PageSection&gt;</code></pre>
    <p>Keeps <code>PageSectionVariants.default</code> enum (still valid in PF6). Clean, consistent approach. <code>hasBodyWrapper={false}</code> ensures children aren't wrapped in an extra <code>PageBody</code> div, matching PF5 behavior.</p>

    <h4>semver/goose approach</h4>
    <p><strong>Inconsistent — three different strategies used across files:</strong></p>
    <pre><code>// Strategy 1: Replace PageSection with &lt;section&gt; (ApplicationDetailsTab)
&lt;section className="co-m-pane__body"&gt;...&lt;/section&gt;

// Strategy 2: Replace with &lt;div&gt; (ApplicationSourcesTab)
&lt;div className="co-m-pane__body"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;

// Strategy 3: Wrap in &lt;Page&gt; + keep PageSection (ApplicationHistoryTab)
&lt;Page&gt;
  &lt;PageSection variant={"default"}&gt;...&lt;/PageSection&gt;
&lt;/Page&gt;</code></pre>

    <table>
      <tr><th>Aspect</th><th><code>pf-codemods</code></th><th><code>semver/goose</code></th></tr>
      <tr class="comparison-row">
        <td>Consistency</td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-green">Consistent</span> — same pattern everywhere</td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-red">Inconsistent</span> — 3 different strategies</td>
      </tr>
      <tr class="comparison-row">
        <td>PF styling preserved</td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-green">Yes</span> — keeps PageSection component</td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-red">Partially</span> — plain <code>&lt;div&gt;</code>/<code>&lt;section&gt;</code> loses PF padding/classes</td>
      </tr>
      <tr class="comparison-row">
        <td>PageSectionVariants removed</td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-orange">No</span> — enum still used (valid but could simplify)</td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-green">Yes</span> — uses string literal <code>"default"</code></td>
      </tr>
    </table>
    <p><strong>Assessment:</strong> pf-codemods has the better PageSection strategy. The <code>hasBodyWrapper={false}</code> approach is documented and preserves PF styling. Replacing PageSection with raw HTML elements is not recommended.</p>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- CSS Token Migration -->
<details>
  <summary>🎨 CSS Token Migration <span class="badge badge-green">Winner: semver/goose</span></summary>
  <div class="details-body">
    <h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>PF6 completely restructures CSS variables: <code>--pf-v5-global--*</code> → <code>--pf-t--global--*</code> (design tokens). The codemods tool replaces color tokens with a hot-pink placeholder <code>--pf-t--temp--dev--tbd</code> that must be manually resolved.</p>

    <h4>Before (main branch)</h4>
    <pre><code>// In TypeScript
export const dangerColor = 'var(--pf-v5-global--danger-color--100)';
export const warningColor = 'var(--pf-v5-global--warning-color--100)';

// In SCSS
stroke: var(--pf-v5-global--success-color--100);
color: var(--pf-v5-global--Color--100) !important;</code></pre>

    <h4>pf-codemods result</h4>
    <pre><code>// Placeholder — NOT a real PF6 token
export const dangerColor = "var(--pf-t--temp--dev--tbd)"
  /* CODEMODS: original v5 color was --pf-v5-global--danger-color--100 */;

// Border value CORRUPTED
border: "var(--pf-t--temp--dev--tbd)"  // Missing "1px solid" prefix!
// Original: border: '1px solid var(--pf-v5-global--BorderColor--200)'</code></pre>

    <h4>semver/goose result</h4>
    <pre><code>// Resolved to real PF6 design tokens
export const dangerColor = 'var(--pf-t--global--color--status--danger--default)';
export const warningColor = 'var(--pf-t--global--color--status--warning--default)';
export const successColor = 'var(--pf-t--global--color--status--success--default)';
export const blueDefaultColor = 'var(--pf-t--global--color--brand--200)';
export const disabledColor = 'var(--pf-t--global--text--color--disabled)';
export const blueInfoColor = 'var(--pf-t--color--blue--40)';

// Border value PRESERVED correctly
border: '1px solid var(--pf-t--global--border--color--200)'

// SCSS also migrated
stroke: var(--pf-t--global--color--status--success--default);
color: var(--pf-t--global--text--color--regular) !important;</code></pre>

    <table>
      <tr><th>Token</th><th><code>pf-codemods</code></th><th><code>semver/goose</code></th></tr>
      <tr class="comparison-row">
        <td><code>--pf-v5-global--danger-color--100</code></td>
        <td><code>--pf-t--temp--dev--tbd</code> ⚠️</td>
        <td><code>--pf-t--global--color--status--danger--default</code> ✓</td>
      </tr>
      <tr class="comparison-row">
        <td><code>--pf-v5-global--success-color--100</code></td>
        <td><code>--pf-t--temp--dev--tbd</code> ⚠️</td>
        <td><code>--pf-t--global--color--status--success--default</code> ✓</td>
      </tr>
      <tr class="comparison-row">
        <td><code>--pf-v5-global--warning-color--100</code></td>
        <td><code>--pf-t--temp--dev--tbd</code> ⚠️</td>
        <td><code>--pf-t--global--color--status--warning--default</code> ✓</td>
      </tr>
      <tr class="comparison-row">
        <td><code>--pf-v5-global--BackgroundColor--200</code></td>
        <td><code>--pf-t--temp--dev--tbd</code> ⚠️</td>
        <td><code>--pf-t--global--background--color--300</code> ✓</td>
      </tr>
