<!-- Modal Migration -->
<details>
  <summary>🪟 Modal Migration (Deprecated → New API) <span class="badge badge-green">Winner: semver/goose</span></summary>
  <div class="details-body">
    <h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>The old Modal was moved to <code>@patternfly/react-core/deprecated</code>. The new Modal (previously at <code>/next</code>) is now the primary export. It uses a composable pattern with <code>ModalHeader</code>, <code>ModalBody</code>, and <code>ModalFooter</code> instead of <code>title</code>/<code>actions</code> props.</p>

    <h4>pf-codemods</h4>
    <pre><code>// NO CHANGE — still using deprecated imports
import { ModalVariant } from '@patternfly/react-core/deprecated';
import { Modal as PfModal } from '@patternfly/react-core/deprecated';</code></pre>

    <h4>semver/goose</h4>
    <pre><code>// Migrated to new composable Modal API
import { Modal as PfModal, ModalBody, ModalFooter, ModalHeader,
         ModalVariant } from '@patternfly/react-core';

&lt;Modal isOpen={isModalOpen} onClose={handleModalClose} variant={ModalVariant.small}&gt;
  &lt;ModalHeader title={t('Add to favorites')} /&gt;
  &lt;ModalBody&gt;
    &lt;Form id="confirm-favorite-form" onSubmit={handleConfirmStar}&gt;...&lt;/Form&gt;
  &lt;/ModalBody&gt;
  &lt;ModalFooter&gt;
    &lt;Button variant="primary"&gt;Save&lt;/Button&gt;
    &lt;Button variant="link"&gt;Cancel&lt;/Button&gt;
  &lt;/ModalFooter&gt;
&lt;/Modal&gt;</code></pre>

    <p><strong>Assessment:</strong> semver/goose correctly migrates to the new composable Modal API per PF6 guidance. pf-codemods leaves the deprecated import untouched.</p>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- React 18 Type Fixes -->
<details>
  <summary>⚛️ React 18 Type Compatibility <span class="badge badge-green">Winner: semver/goose</span></summary>
