    <li><strong>Fix SplitItem <code>component</code> prop misuse</strong> in <code>ResourceRow.tsx</code> — revert to using <code>children</code> (the <code>component</code> prop sets the wrapper element type, not content).</li>
    <li><strong>Review PageSection replacements</strong> — the 2 instances where PageSection was replaced with <code>&lt;div&gt;</code>/<code>&lt;section&gt;</code> (ApplicationDetailsTab, ApplicationSourcesTab) should use <code>PageSection</code> with <code>hasBodyWrapper={false}</code> instead to preserve PF styling.</li>
    <li><strong>Review <code>EmptyState titleText=""</code></strong> — empty string is technically valid but should contain a meaningful label for accessibility.</li>
  </ol>

  <h4>Optional improvements:</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Validate <code>--pf-t--color--blue--40</code> is a valid PF6 token (may need <code>--pf-t--global--color--nonstatus--blue--300</code> instead)</li>
    <li>Add <code>.cache*</code> to <code>.gitignore</code></li>
    <li>Migrate remaining 12 old-style <code>pf-c-*</code> SCSS selectors (shared tech debt)</li>
    <li>Consider using <code>hasBodyWrapper={false}</code> from pf-codemods for the remaining PageSection instances that wrap in <code>&lt;Page&gt;</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Why not pf-codemods?</h4>
  <p>While pf-codemods builds cleanly, it represents only the <em>first step</em> of migration (running the codemod tool) without the essential <em>second step</em> (resolving placeholders, migrating CSS classes, updating deprecated APIs). The 12 <code>--pf-t--temp--dev--tbd</code> tokens would cause visual regressions at runtime (hot-pink or invisible colors). The 2 corrupted border values would break layout. It leaves 33+ pf-v5 references that will silently stop working. It's a starting point, not a shippable migration.</p>
</div>

